	<div class="blog-archive-entries-wrapper">
		<div id="unique-entry-id-402" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">I hope everyone enjoyed today.</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Friday, 29 April 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-side-tracked.php">Side Tracked</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="books" src="books.jpg" width="42" height="40" /></div>I hope everyone enjoyed today.  Being someone who loves getting lost in the land of books, I loved the Royal Wedding, as it is a bit like a fairy tale coming to life.  Someone who as a child, like us, watched the royalty from a distance is now married to a prince.<br /><br />I really do hope they have a long and happy marriage and the press leave them in peace and do not destroy another marriage.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-401" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Immortal War</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Thursday, 21 April 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>From Justin Somper's Twitter.<br />"Finished the proof-read on IMMORTAL WAR. Phew! Just in time for Easter. Desperately owe the Nocturnals a blog too!"<br /><br />Yipee, one step closer hearing about what happens next.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-400" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Twitter</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Monday, 18 April 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>Being rather slow ... JustinSomper wrote on Twitter.<br />"Much looking forward to the FCBG conference this weekend? Tweet me if you're going to be there <img class="blog-image-smiley" src="../../../rw_common/plugins/blog/smiley_wink.png" width="21" height="21" alt="Winking" border="0" />"<br />It's the Federation Of Children Book Groups and their conference was over the whole weekend.  I just hope everyone enjoyed themselves.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-399" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Easter Holidays</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Monday, 18 April 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-side-tracked.php">Side Tracked</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="books" src="books.jpg" width="42" height="40" /></div>I have not really spent enough time here lately.  I noticed I forgot to publish the last blog entries - sorry, and now it is the holidays I am rather behind in general.<br />Sorry Everyone.<br /><br />I do hope you all checked out your local libraries for activities.  My kids made shields and monsters!  Yes I now have found and entered our local library and read all three Time Raiders books from there.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-398" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Ma Kettle</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Sunday, 10 April 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="Me as Ma Kettle" src="MaKettleSq.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></div>I asked during the question and answer session whether Ma Kettle would get her own back over what happened to Lucky.  As it was a bit obvious that I was probably the only one in the audiance who has read all the books, I got the reaction just wait for the book to come out.  I am really hoping that she does in her own way, but like us all I am waiting .... <br /><br /><br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-397" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Oxford Literary Festival</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Saturday, 09 April 2011 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="category-justin-somper.php">Justin Somper</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><img class="imageStyle" alt="" src="page73_blog_entry397_1.jpg" width="80" height="80" />Justin Somper was at the Oxford Literary Festival today.  My daughter and I had a wonderful day together in Oxford, hunting down our tickets and seeing his show.<br /><br />If you ever get the chance of going to see an author is it well worth it, even if it is just a signing.<br /></div></div>
	</div>
	
	 
